import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median Age: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['gender'])
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.pie(gender_counts, labels=gender_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, colors=['#ff9999','#66b3ff'])
    ax.axis('equal')
    ax.set_title('What is the gender distribution of the deceased individuals?')
    ax.legend(title='Gender', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['race'])
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts(normalize=True)
    ax = sns.barplot(x=race_counts.index, y=race_counts.values)
    ax.set(xlabel='Race', ylabel='Proportion')
    ax.axhline(y=race_counts.mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
